FirstGroup CEO Bonus Package Is Rejected by 42% of Shareholders

-- B y   N i d a a   B a k h s h
-- 
2011-07-16T07:31:24Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-16/firstgroup-ceo-bonus-package-is-rejected-by-42-of-shareholders.html
A minority of shareholders rejected
a proposed bonus package for Tim O’Toole, the chief executive
officer of  FirstGroup Plc (FGP) , the U.K.’s biggest train operator,
the Guardian newspaper reported.  About 42 percent of shareholders voted against the award of
215,000 shares, the newspaper said yesterday, citing the
company.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nidaa Bakhsh in London at 
